headline: Materials Stocks, Copper Jump After Freeport-McMoRan Earnings. Charts Point to More Upside Ahead.
summary: Materials stocks and copper are in focus today, with  Freeport-McMoRan  trading higher after delivering better-than-expected quarterly results.  The  which holds  Freeport-McMoRan  as its fourth-largest position, is up close to 2% since the open.  Copper prices have been climbing steadily after the late-July tariff-driven selloff and are now consolidating in a bull flag pattern near the key $5.00 level.
